SIMPLE: interrupted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interrupted
<hw>In`ter*rupt"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Broken;
intermitted; suddenly stopped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Irregular; -- said of any
arrangement whose symmetry is destroyed by local causes, as when
leaflets are interposed among the leaves in a pinnate leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interruptedly</ent>⟦br⟧
